{"questionId":"22457284","questionHtml":"<p>Consider a random variable <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>Determine the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>correct inequality or equation involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempts to solve their inequality (equality) involving&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Valid solving attempts include graphical, use of logarithms, tabular or trial and error.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0078</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0078</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A2)</em></strong></p>\n<p>the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>010022</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(corresponding to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0075169</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>corresponding to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;(which is the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (TABLE ONLY APPROACH)</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use binomial cdf to calculate a correct value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;for one value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>calculates correct values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> for at least one value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>989977</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(corresponding to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>992483</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>corresponding to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;(which is the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[5 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22457284","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.5","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Consider a random variable X such that X~Bn, 0.25. Determine the least value of n such that PX≥1>0.99.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}